                               <p style="font-size: 19px; color: black; font-style: italic;">"The only way to do great work is to love what you do. If you haven't found it yet, keep looking. Don't settle." ~Steve Jobs                            </p>



                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            Christian Dior, a globally renowned fashion designer, has a luxury fashion brand of his own. The world's top models and actors dream of wearing his brand's clothes. Sounds dreamy, doesn't it? What if I told you that Christian Dior established the House of Dior when he was 41 years old? He started garnering fame and success only after his 40s. We know him and his brand today solely because he followed his dream and passion and displayed perseverance. 

                        </p>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            At least someone must have asked you this question by now, "So, what do you want to do when you grow up?" If this question leads you to worry about your future career, you have come to the right place. We have listed down a few factors that can help you choose your career. The aspects you need to consider are:
                            
                            <br><br>
                                        1. Confronting parental pressure.
                                    
                                <br>
                                        2. Avoiding peer influence.
                                    
                                <br>
                                        3. Recognising your interests and hobbies.
                                    
                                <br>
                                        4. Building a career based on your strengths.
                                    
                                <br>
                                        5. Shortlist your career options and research the shortlisted options. 
                                    
                                    <br>
                                
                            
                        </p>
                        <div class="row" >
                            <div class="col-lg-12 col-12" style="padding: 0 0 0 0;" >
