<br><br>
                        <H3 style=" font-style: underline">1. <u>Confront Parental Pressure:</u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                        
                        It is perfectly alright to seek your parents' guidance while deciding on a career path, but you must ensure that your chosen career is primarily based on your interests. Pursuing a career of your parents' interest will do you more harm than good if your interest does not lie in that field. Try Communicating with your parents and have a healthy conversation with them. 
                    
                        <br><br>
                                1. Provide them with reasons why you are not comfortable pursuing a career of their choice.
                            
                        <br>
                                2. Mention the career you aim to pursue and highlight how you can excel in that field with your skills and abilities. 

                            
                        
                        </p>

                        <br>
                        <H3 style="font-style: underline">2.<u> Avoid Getting Influenced by your Peers:                         </u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            We often get swayed by our friends' opinions and career choices. When deciding your career path, the choice should solely be yours. Remember that your friends' lives are starkly different from yours. No one is walking on the same track as you, so you need to figure out a career that suits you best. Be cautious of your career choices and question yourself on whether you are getting influenced by peer pressure. If yes, rethink your decision. 

                        </p>

                        <div class="row" >
                            <div class="col-lg-12 col-12" style="padding: 0 0 0 0;" >
                                <img alt="image" class="blogimg" src="https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/waves-36bb5.appspot.com/o/14.jpg?alt=media&token=3110da37-3095-4c02-83b8-e17f172de2fa" >
                            </div>
                            </div>
                        <br>
                        <H3 style="font-style: underline">3.<u> Seek Career Counselling: 
                        </u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            We often get swayed by our friends' opinions and career choices. When deciding your career path, the choice should solely be yours. Remember that your friends' lives are starkly different from yours. No one is walking on the same track as you, so you need to figure out a career that suits you best. Be cautious of your career choices and question yourself on whether you are getting influenced by peer pressure. If yes, rethink your decision. 

                        </p>

                        <br>
                        <H3 style=" font-style: underline">4.<u> Identify your Interests and Hobbies:</u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            There is nothing better than paving a career path based on things you enjoy doing. So, take a closer look at your interests and hobbies. Ask yourself these questions:  
                        
                            <br><br>
                               1. What do I do the most during my free time? 
   </ls>
                        <br>
                                2. Where do my interests lie? (in music, drawing, dance, languages, communication, debating, cooking, or solving logical questions?)

                            
                        <br>
                               3. What are the things that I really enjoy doing?  
                            
                        
                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            Once you list down your interests, examine whether you can pursue a career based on them. For instance, someone passionate about cooking and who loves experimenting with new dishes can pursue a course on hotel management and aim to become a chef in well-established companies like Taj. 

                        </p>
                        </p>

                        <br>
                        <H3 style="font-style: underline">5.<u> Build a Career Based on your Strengths:

                        </u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            It is advisable to choose a career option where you can utilise your strengths to the fullest. Be cautious to not play with your weaknesses while deciding on a suitable career option. So, if you are great at communicating with people and managing interactions, then taking up Public Relations (PR) jobs, Human Resources (HR) jobs, or positions in Marketing departments of companies would be beneficial for you. 
                        </p>
                        <div class="row" >
                            <div class="col-lg-12 col-12" style="padding: 0 0 0 0;" >
