                            </div>
                            </div>
                        <br>
                        <H3 style="font-style: underline">6.<u> Shortlist your Career Options: 


                        </u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            As mentioned before, it is crucial to recognise your interests, hobbies and passions while deciding on a career path. Based on these interests, you can shortlist a few career options you would like to pursue. Creating this list would help you narrow down your focus to a limited set of options instead of going astray and getting confused with multiple options in mind. 
  </p>

  <br>
                        <H3 style=" font-style: underline">7.<u> Conduct Research on the Shortlisted Options: 
                            </u>
                        </H3>

                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                        
                            Once you are done shortlisting a few career options, the next step is to conduct adequate research on these fields. This is the most crucial step in deciding on a good career path. It would help you get a realistic picture of how the professions you wish to pursue work in the real world. The aspects that you could research in your chosen fields would include: 
                            <br><br>
                            
                                1. The options of courses/degrees that would lead you toward your dream job 
                          
                            <br>
                                2. The institutions that offer these courses (in India and abroad)
 

                            <br>
                                3. The qualifications required to take up the job of your interest

                                <br>
                                4. The financial cost involved in pursuing the courses


                                <br>
                                5. The range of job opportunities that these courses or degrees offer. 

                        </p>
                        <p style="padding: 0px 0px 3% 0px;font-size: 23px;color: black; font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif,';">
                            These tips would surely help you gain a clearer perspective on the kind of job opportunities you wish to pursue in your career. We have many more interesting tips lined up for you in the upcoming blog. So stay tuned! See you soon :)

                        </p>





